.TH "snd_hdac_stream_sync" 9 "snd_hdac_stream_sync" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_stream_sync \- sync with start/strop trigger operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_hdac_stream_sync
.BI "(struct hdac_stream *azx_dev "  ","
.BI "bool start "  ","
.BI "unsigned int streams "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "azx_dev" 12
HD-audio core stream (master stream)
.IP "start" 12
true = start, false = stop
.IP "streams" 12
bit flags of streams to sync
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For \fIstart\fP = true, wait until all FIFOs get ready.
For \fIstart\fP = false, wait until all RUN bits are cleared.
